	<td bgcolor="#000000" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Well, I hate to add this to the lists of I wonder.... But, the fact that agro with taunt as a yes | no would be the simplest thing to do of course and somewhat expected, and I guess even what the community was told how taunt worked?  Is that realistic?  Well, I know we are not talking about other games but please hear me out, as this is true even in the EQ Pencil and Paper game.<br />
<br />
Taunt is nothing but a bluff, it is not real, you are using words or gestures to upset the way an enemy thinks, to somehow make them believe that if they don't kill you first they are in trouble.  When we look at it that way lets now say that the intelligence or fighting "experience" of said mob matters.  They would have a counter check to your bluff that says for example, "Brutul is full of shit the cleric has done all the damage anyways why would I hit him, I'll stick to the cleric."  This would be completetly true no?  Hence it would take a lot of convincing (multiple successfull taunts) to make that creature think different?<br />
<br />
Before anyone starts calling me stupid please realize these are just ideas, since there seems to be something ominous about the way taunt works.  Aside from this theory there are many others that friends of mine have offered such as:  tuant is CHA based?, taunt is INT based?  Wis Based? there is a counter mob check for realism?  The dummer the mob the more responsive to just taunt?<br />
<br />
Granted is this method of thinking more realistic?  Yes, specially since they've given the oportunity to increase those stats thru AA's, but when things work that way there is usually a skill that improves it, no not AETaunt, more along the lines of (Brutish all your taunt checks will now be based on STR instead of XX skill)  That btw is one of their skills on the pencil and paper version of EQ.  <br />
<br />
Anyways, just thought I'd add my 2 coppers which by no means I say are law just throwing out ideas to the masses.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >__________________<br>
