	<td bgcolor="#000000" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post22038"></a>
	

	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><font color=""><b>Aethor</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >knows that Warriors are superior</font><br>
	<p>
&nbsp;<br>
<a href="showthread.php?postid=22038#post22038"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Post #21</font></a><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >Registered: May 2003<br>
	Posts: 9<br><br>



	Server: <br>





                Guild: <br>



<br>	
</td>
	<td bgcolor="#000000" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b>Taunt works over any amount of agro</b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >I can confirm it. 65 Sk here, browsing boards due to boredom...<br />
<br />
Anyhow. Last week we killed the Arch Lich, and at the time two of our best warriors weren't online. Now, we do tank him with SKs and paladins as well, but we wanted to use a warrior so that the warriors who were there get some practice.<br />
<br />
After clearing other snakes in AL room,  everyone was medding/rebuffing in the corner behind the pillar as needed, I went to the beginning of the ramp and started chain casting two best agro spells I have (but only those spells that won't damage the mob so it doesn't go into summon mode before we want it).<br />
<br />
I casted it for something like 5 to 8 minutes. We had 3 warriors at the time, and two of them were very new - one was actually a potential recruit, completely untested, so the raid leader decided to put them all in MT lineup to see how will they behave. <br />
<br />
At least one of them does not have AE taunt for sure, I don't know about other two.<br />
<br />
The last on MT list was then told to go to AL and not attack at all, just to click taunt repeatedly until he gets hit, then to run back to us. I stopped casting, and I had built insane agro at the time.  (Imagine a SK chaincasting agro for 8 minutes without stopping and without doing anything else) He did as he was told, voila, he got (insane agro) + 1.<br />
<br />
Then I continued for another 3-5 min and the second warrior in MT line was told to do the same, now he had (insane agro * 1.5) + 1<br />
<br />
Then I continued building agro.<br />
<br />
Then the first MT was told to do the same, with the exception that he wasn't supposed to run back, but continue attacking and we started on AL... he had (insane agro)*2 + 1.<br />
<br />
<b>Yes, taunt worked in all 3 cases.</b> And I had sufficient agro built to break any possible limit or cap there is - <b>which means there isn't one.</b><br />
<br />
After that, the warrior who was first MT had AL simply glued to him for the rest of the fight. He didn't die - we have set the MT order up just in case, to be 100 percent sure who gets next agro, this is why they were taunting and running away.<br />
<br />
The agro on MT didn't move for one single moment.<br />
<br />
Note that it usually wasn't enough to click taunt once - they were clicking it till they got hit by AL, it took some amount of clicking, but at the end they were able to start the fight with an amount of agro that allows them to keep the mob on them regardless of what do their weapons proc, or not proc at all.<br />
<br />
<br />
Aethor<br />
<br />
65 Shadowknight<br />
The Nameless</font></p>
	
