	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >That's interesting Aethor.  Although it could have had something to do with distance to the mob. <br />
<br />
<blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >quote:</font><hr>Of course it could be something as simple as the assumtion that the verbal responce from the mob does not represent a successful taunt. It could be that mobs are ware of ALL taunts and respond randomly to any taunt message. <br />
<br />
Are there anytimes in your log that you got agro from taunt without a message?<br />
<br />
I have never much gotten into agro theories becuase alot of people run with the assumption that responce = successful taunt and I have never seen that justified.<hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
I would bet a large amount of cash that message = successful taunt.  Up until last night I have always been absolutely confident that I had aggro after a successful taunt.  I have grouped with other tanks and hybrids and seen mobs turn on them like clockwork after seeing their name in the "I'll teach you to interfere" message.  The main difference last night is that I am not usually *that* far behind anyone in my group on aggro. <br />
<br />
<blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >quote:</font><hr>As far as I know there have been NO developer statements on taunt that I know of. And I think you have a heck of an idea there that could be a 3rd possiblity of not getting agro on a succesful taunt.<br />
<hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
There was a developer statement on taunt and they said it worked as we have explained it does on this board (moves you to the top of the hate list if successful).<br />
<br />
<blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >quote:</font><hr>1) Responce to taunt is independent of success of taunt check.<br />
2) Responce is indicative of a successful taunt but it only adds a flat amount. There for a succesful taunt does not automagically move you to the top of the list.<br />
3) Mobs responced to a successful tuant, but then then get a save.<br />
<hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
My bet would be #2.  Taunt moves you to the top of the hate list, as the developers told us it did long ago, but perhaps there is a maximum amount of hate you can get from a successful taunt.<br />
<br />
<blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >quote:</font><hr>Wait a min...<br />
<br />
I remember VI saying something about spells having a maximum +hate value based upon the hp of the mob, could it be that they were just lazy and capped the taunt skill like they did spells?<hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
Another interesting thought.  That could explain Aethor's anecdote.<br />
<br />
Would definitely like to get some more tests done on this subject now.  Anyone that knows of some good "talking" mobs that have enough hitpoints that they could take a few stuns from my cleric but not tough enough that they will kill him before he can get decent aggro built up would be appreciated.  I have a raid tonight but if it's not to late when it gets over I will give some freeport guards a try afterwards.</font></p>
	
