	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Hmm but then if a successful taunt adds a fixed amount, how did warrior MTs in exp groups, after they taunt the mob I pull off of me, sometimes, right after successfully taking agro, lose the agro when I make just a hit or two with two-hander?<br />
<br />
Then that fixed amount of agro is very low... or the entire system works in some other way...?<br />
<br />
However, I have some possible explanations for your experiment with the cleric.<br />
<br />
Spells produce agro. Spells also need time to cast. If the cleric casted something (like a nuke or stun) on the mob, in mid-cast you taunted and you got agro but then the spell lanted in next second... the mob turns back to him.<br />
<br />
Note in your log that at first the cleric was casting after you taunted, then he remember that he shouldn't cast.<br />
<br />
What about healing? If he healed himself, the healing itself produces agro...<br />
<br />
The entire log looks to me (I might be wrong however) as if the cleric produced agro right after your taunt... or at the same time, although after the initial "forgot no casting" and "I ducked" there isn't anything about him casting...  what about heal over time spells? Damage shields (cleric MoK/MoR spells)? How would they affect agro?<br />
<br />
Aethor<br />
<br />
65 Shadowknight<br />
The Nameless</font></p>
	
